title: Magnitude 4.6 quake shakes Davao, 2 hurt
text:
Nation ( Leaderboard Top ), pagematch: 1, sectionmatch: 1 Magnitude 4.6 quake shakes Davao, 2 hurt By Rosette Adel (philstar.com) | Updated February 23, 2017 - 12:02pm Phivolcs said the tremor which occurred at 9:50 a.m. was felt at Intensity IV in Davao City. Phivolcs 
MANILA, Philippines â€“ The Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) on Thursday morning reported that a magnitude 4.6 earthquake jolted Davao City. 
In its 10 a.m. advisory, Phivolcs said the tremor which occurred at 9:50 a.m. was felt at Intensity IV in Davao City. It was considered moderately strong felt by people indoors and outdoors. 
Reports said the quake damaged a waiting shed leaving two people hurt. 
The quake was also felt at Intensity I in Kidapawan City. 
Phivolcs traced the epicenter of the quake at 9 kilometers north west of Davao City, Davao del Sur. It has a depth of focus of 15 kilometers. 
No aftershock is expected in the quake determined to be tectonic in origin. Nation ( Article MRec ), pagematch: 1, sectionmatch: 1
